rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to be good. I start working more hours this week at my "full time job" and I get to spend more time at home with my dog and sister. I feel like I will be able to make dinner every night and keep the house cleaner now.
critical_positive: What worked well was that it was light. We both had pets and she likes animals, so I knew that she was a person that I would like. She also has an autistic son and I'm a behavioral therapist, so I knew that would make us click. There was an age difference and we are different races, but we did briefly talk about the struggles of being a woman in tech. She was awesome.
critical_negative: Honestly, I don't really think anything didn't work well. We both talked a lot and shared parts of our story with each other. We laughed a lot. I think she had a great sense of humor and I think in the "real world" we would get a long a lot.

rest_of_day_open: I see a lot of work in the rest of the week (i'm going to count through next friday, since it's saturday), but maybe i'll be able to have some relaxation over the weekend. the weather probably won't cooperate, though. We got a lot of good work done on froday at my job, so maybe monday/etc. will be smoother?
critical_positive: the chat platform worked really well, both video and sound, and it was great having a convo with someone who was interesting and interested in being there. She was engaging and had a pretty cute dog who interrupted. :) we found a lot of things in common, and it was neat to connect with someone in this way.
critical_negative: i'm not sure, honestly. there's always some awkwardness when two people who don't know each other start in on a conversation. but once you get past "hi how are you what's your name" you can find something to latch on to where there's something in common. and right now the whole country has something in common...
